parameters: There's a message from the headquarters...

You've really done well this time. The data you
sent has been broadcasted overseas and is causing
a big stir. Although, it probably won't be
reported domestically...

However, during the diversion operation earlier,
some of our comrades were unable to escape and
were captured by the imperial soldiers. They will
likely be tortured to extract information. We need
to somehow rescue them. We know where they are
being held.

The people who were captured because of my
strategy... Damn it!

Is she... asleep? Maybe I should check the
computer...
No way... You did it to help me...

It's not Esuka's fault. It's because of my
strategy...

Shuu... No, this is both of our faults. We will
definitely make this mission a success!

I equipped Esuka with an external battery. It
should be useful in battle.

You're quite something, as expected of the
professor!

(I have a bad feeling about this, but I have no
choice but to trust Esuka...)

Really, you've done it quite extravagantly,
Esuka... Stop jumping off high-rise buildings.
I'm sorry, Doctor, it's my responsibility.
Anyway, thank goodness you're safe, Esuka.

Wh-what are you waiting for... hurry up and
perform maintenance.

Good grief, as you said, I've forwarded the data
sent from Esuka to headquarters. I've already
received a response from them.
The maintenance will take a little longer.

Alright, it's about time to finish the
maintenance.
